{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "2c6b6bcc61203fc3", "candidate": {"id": "cand-027", "name": "Sophie Williams", "raw_cv": "SOPHIE WILLIAMS\nsophie.williams@email.com | London, UK\n\nPLATFORM ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nPlatform engineer with 6 years of experience building developer tooling and cloud infrastructure on GCP and AWS. Strong focus on observability, reliability engineering, and internal platform products. Open source contributor to OpenTelemetry.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nPlatform Engineer \u2014 Deliveroo, London (2021\u2013present)\n- Own the observability platform used by 300+ engineers (Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, Tempo)\n- Built a self-service SLO management tool adopted by 60 teams, replacing manual dashboard creation\n- Led GCP \u2192 multi-cloud strategy work, introducing AWS S3/Lambda for specific workloads\n- Designed and shipped the internal secrets management migration (Vault \u2192 GCP Secret Manager + custom operator)\n- OpenTelemetry contributor: merged 3 PRs to the Go SDK\n\nPlatform Engineer \u2014 Babylon Health, London (2018\u20132021)\n- Built CI/CD infrastructure on GCP (Cloud Build, Artifact Registry, GKE)\n- Designed the internal microservice scaffolding CLI used by all backend teams\n- Introduced chaos engineering practice (Gremlin) and ran first gameday\n\nSKILLS\nGCP, AWS, Kubernetes, Terraform, Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, Tempo, OpenTelemetry, Go, Python, Bash, Vault, Helm, ArgoCD, GitHub Actions, Cloud Build\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Physics \u2014 Imperial College London (2013\u20132016)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "Platform engineer at Deliveroo focused on observability and developer experience. I build the tools that let 300+ engineers understand what their systems are doing at any moment. I'm an OpenTelemetry contributor and I think distributed tracing is one of the most underused tools in the reliability engineering kit. I started in physics which I think gave me a good intuition for measurement and uncertainty. Looking for senior platform or SRE roles where observability is a first-class concern. London-based.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Sophie, tell me about the SLO management tool you built.\n\nSophie: Before the tool, SLOs at Deliveroo were aspirational \u2014 teams nominally had them but there was no consistent way to define, track, or alert on them. I built a Kubernetes operator that reads SLO definitions from Git (as CRDs), automatically provisions the Prometheus recording rules and Grafana dashboards, and sends a weekly SLO report to the team's Slack channel. The whole thing is declarative. A team can go from no SLO to a working one in about 10 minutes. 60 teams are using it now.\n\nInterviewer: What drew you to observability as a specialism?\n\nSophie: Honestly, a production incident at Babylon that we spent 6 hours debugging because we had no traces. We had logs and metrics but no way to follow a request across our 20+ microservices. I spent the next month instrumenting everything with Jaeger and the next incident of the same type took 20 minutes to diagnose. That hooked me. I became the resident expert and then started contributing to OpenTelemetry because I wanted to understand the standard deeply.\n\nInterviewer: This role involves significant Kubernetes platform work alongside observability. Is that balance right for you?\n\nSophie: Yes \u2014 I think observability in isolation is only half the picture. Understanding the infrastructure means you understand what you're observing. I want to stay in a role where I'm doing both.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nSophie: I'm at \u00a388,000 at Deliveroo. I'd be looking for \u00a395\u2013102,000.", "years_experience": 6.0, "skills": ["GCP", "AWS", "Kubernetes", "Terraform", "Prometheus", "Grafana", "Loki", "Tempo", "OpenTelemetry", "Go", "Python", "Bash", "Vault", "Helm", "ArgoCD", "GitHub Actions", "Cloud Build", "distributed tracing", "chaos engineering", "reliability engineering", "observability", "SRE"], "industries": ["technology", "healthcare (Babylon)", "food delivery (Deliveroo)"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.88, "culture_fit_score": 0.82, "constraints": [{"id": "ca60ac79", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary at Deliveroo is \u00a388,000 (mentioned in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 88000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "a5f50fc7", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking minimum salary of \u00a395,000 (interview stated range \u00a395\u2013102k)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "9c515728", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking maximum salary of \u00a3102,000 (interview stated range \u00a395\u2013102k)", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 102000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "9b555a95", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_function", "description": "Prefers roles balancing Kubernetes platform engineering with observability work; both areas important", "canonical_key": null, "value": "balance of Kubernetes platform work with observability", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93, "currency": null}, {"id": "3ed409c4", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "London-based and interested in London roles", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "London", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "ad0a32ce", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "British citizen; does not require visa sponsorship", "canonical_key"